<br>
The truth is that your starting stat points will be absolutely insignificant throughout your career, for 2 main reasons:<br>
<br>
1. Stats have VERY little impact on your performance.<br>
2. During your career you will have the opportunity to gain hundreds of points of stat bonuses - many times the points you start with.<br>
<br>
At Level 60, each point of STA is only about 4 extra hit points - so 20 points in STA will yield 80 extra hit points. This is absolutely meaningless when fighting creatures that hit for 250-500+ with each blow, or cast spells for 1,000+ damage. The only reason why the current consensus advises putting starting points in STA is that this is the hardest stat to raise with gear.<br>
<br>
Just use an equipment strategy that gets you what is of most benefit as you advance, and pay attention to key stat threshholds - for example, if your STA is below 100 you will take a 10 point stat penalty to STR, DEX, and AGI when you become fatigued. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wubao>Wubao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1078<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/19/02 9:42:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1713.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting Stats</span><hr size=1> Most monks I know didn't put any of their starting points into CHARISMA, and they're still ok after 50 some odd levels.<br>
